channel.title: Need Professional's HELP!
channel.description: OK to begin with this is my 4th FULL day trying to make my server online so other people can play. I've Port Forwarded Correctly i believe because when i check my port it says OPEN. I've also port forwarded with Utorrent and after Utorrent it worked once but i wanted to change Sources so after i did that it stopped working. I don't know what else to say, If you can help PLEASE DO SO i will return the favor. If you need more info PLEASE ask and i also Have Team Viewer! Thanks! [center][size=14pt]PLEASE HELP![/size][/center]

item.title: Need Professional's HELP!
item.dc:creator: @GoranTheSerb GoranTheSerb
item.description:
@GoranTheSerb wrote:

[quote=“xtylerr, post:2, topic:373340”]You don’t really need a no-ip… I don’t use one and my server is online and working great.

Just go into firewall settings, open up a new port, and set that port to your server.

Then change your server’s ip address to your own ip.[/quote]
Can you teamview me this?
